The paper deals with video object codetection, which is a problem in computer vision. The use of weak semantic constraints and pairing videos with sentences suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques to improve performance suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of videos and frames suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of semantic information suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
